// mobile/ios/Config/Production.xcconfig
//
// PR-Sprint7-Item-13 (MOB-6) ŌĆö Production (release / distribution) build
// configuration.
//
// This file is wired in via `baseConfigurationReference` on the Release
// build configurations in `Runner.xcodeproj/project.pbxproj` for the
// Runner + OpenE2eeTunnelProvider targets (H4, H6). It holds the real
// Apple Developer Team ID for signed App Store / Test Flight / Ad Hoc
// distribution builds.
//
// DESIGN POSTURE: the placeholder is intentionally NOT a real value.
// --------------------------------------------------------------------
// The repository must never carry a real Team ID (it is a credential
// tied to a paying Apple Developer Program membership and is revolvable
// per-org). This file ships with a deliberately invalid placeholder so
// `flutter build ios --release` will FAIL in CI until an operator
// supplies the real value via the documented procedure (see
// `docs/SETUP-iOS.md`). This is the same fail-closed posture used for
// `JWT_SECRET` (Sprint 5 PR-32) and `REDIS_PASSWORD` (Sprint 7
// SEC-6/7) ŌĆö a missing/invalid secret must abort the build, never
// silently embed an empty value.
//
// HOW TO POPULATE
// ---------------
// 1. Open `https://developer.apple.com/account/#!/membership` (App
//    Store Connect ŌåÆ Membership) and copy the 10-character Team ID
//    (e.g. `ABCDE12345`).
// 2. Replace the `REPLACE_WITH_YOUR_APPLE_DEVELOPER_TEAM_ID` value
//    below with that string ŌĆö keep the trailing semicolon, do not add
//    quotes (xcconfig treats the value as a literal string already).
// 3. CI users: pass the value via a build-time environment variable
//    in the macOS-latest leg of `.github/workflows/ios.yml`. The
//    recommended pattern is:
//      - Run `xcodegen` (or hand-edit) so the xcconfig reads
//        `TEAMS_IDENTIFIER = $(OPENE2EE_TEAMS_IDENTIFIER)` and the
//        GitHub Action exports the secret into the build environment.
//      - OR keep the placeholder literal here and let CI overwrite it
//        via a `sed` step in a pre-build phase.
//    See `docs/SETUP-iOS.md` ┬¦3 for the exact run-script shape.
//
// Pre-flight (from ios-native-bridging.md)
// ----------------------------------------
// Verify before changing `baseConfigurationReference`:
//   * This file is referenced by PBXFileReference UUID BD in pbxproj.
//   * It is the base config for XCBuildConfiguration entries H4
//     (Runner Release) and H6 (OpenE2eeTunnelProvider Release). The
//     Debug + test configurations point at `Local.xcconfig` instead.

TEAMS_IDENTIFIER = REPLACE_WITH_YOUR_APPLE_DEVELOPER_TEAM_ID
OPENE2EE_BUILD_ENVIRONMENT = production